Europe has won the Ryder Cup in Paris
The European team won the 2018 Ryder Cup, defeating the USA team 16.5:10.5 at Le Gold National outside Paris.
The U.S. has now lost six straight times on the European stage and hasn't won a Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe defended their title as Danish captain Thomas Bjørn's team scored the 14.5 points needed to beat the United States.
Phil Mickelson, the American star, who had been struggling all tournament, dropped his par-3 shot on the 16th hole, giving Francesco Molinari the win.
The Italian golfer Molinari has excelled in all of the events, becoming one of only four players to ever achieve a 5-0-0 record since the tournament began in its current form in 1979.
The American Jordan Spieth was beaten 5-4 by the lowest ranked player in the European team, the Dane Thorbjørn Olsen.
Dustin Johnson, one of the best players in the world, lost 2-1 to England's Ian Poulter, who may have been on his last Ryder Cup.
Eight-time Ryder Cup veteran Sergio Garcia of Spain is the tournament's all-time leading scorer with 25.5 career points.
